*** The FIDE World Championship ***

A legendary cycle unbroken for 135 years


Magnus Carlsen, the highest-rated chess player of all time, and the FIDE World Champion since 2013 takes on Ian Nepomniachtchi, Carlsen's former second, and one of the only grandmasters with a winning record against Carlsen.

This November, be a part of chess history.



THE CHAMPIONSHIP MATCHUP

The Champion

** Magnus Carlsen
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- FIDE World Champion since 2013
- Highest rating of all time
- World #1 for over 10 years
- Undefeated for a record 125 consecutive games (Between 2018-2020)

Peak Rating - 2882
Country - Norway
Age - 30


The Challenger

** Ian Nepomniachtchi
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Won the 2010 and 2020 Russian Superfinal
- Has plus score against Carlsen
- Russia’s #1 chess player

Peak Rating - 2792
Country - Russia
Age - '31'


WHEN + WHERE TO TUNE IN

Chess.com is thrilled to announce that GM Fabiano Caruana, the 2018 world championship challenger, #1 rated American chess player, and longtime #2 player in the world, will be a Chess.com commentator for the 2021 FIDE World Championship!

When is the Championship?
- Wed, Nov 24, 2021 – Thu, Dec 16, 2021

How Should You Tune In?
- Chess.com is the best way for you to enjoy the ultimate chess match. With a team of heavyweight commentators and live camera feeds on all broadcasts, you won't miss a single detail of the event.

And Not to Mention...
- Our live video access (exclusive on Twitch) will make you feel like you're right there in the playing hall with the players, so be sure to tune in!


